description:
The Congos’ Lee “Scratch” Perry-produced and mixed roots evergreen is one you’d play to aliens enquiring about reggae. It returns to vinyl orbit with VP Records for the umpteenth time, primed for any shelf - as essential as they come.

It’s hard to overstate the classic status of ‘Heart of the Congos’, which was recorded at Lee Perry’s legendary Black Ark in 1977, and has endured as a staple of the reggae canon ever since. The trio of “Ashanti” Roy Johnson (tenor), Cedric Myton (falsetto) and... more
